1
00:00:04,004 --> 00:00:06,472
PREVIOUSLY ON <i>TATSUKI: TOO KIND FOR SCHOOL</i>

2
00:00:06,473 --> 00:00:10,010
I was his homeroom teacher.

3
00:00:10,677 --> 00:00:11,678
I'm…

4
00:00:12,412 --> 00:00:14,413
- going to end my life here.
- I won't allow it.

5
00:00:14,414 --> 00:00:17,282
Trash… will always be trash.

6
00:00:17,283 --> 00:00:18,817
It will forever be trash.

7
00:00:18,818 --> 00:00:20,119
You're not trash.

8
00:00:20,120 --> 00:00:22,654
- Please save Tomoki.
- What?

9
00:00:22,655 --> 00:00:24,990
I think Tomoki
is planning to kill himself.

10
00:00:24,991 --> 00:00:26,292
<i>So please save him right now.</i>

11
00:00:27,660 --> 00:00:28,495
Tomoki!

12
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:36,036
Tatsuki. Tatsuki!

13
00:00:36,603 --> 00:00:37,536
SHIZUKU AOMINE

14
00:00:37,537 --> 00:00:39,638
Tatsuki is… Tatsuki is…

15
00:00:39,639 --> 00:00:41,140
Stop the bleeding immediately!

16
00:00:41,141 --> 00:00:42,107
I can't do it.

17
00:00:42,108 --> 00:00:43,276
<i>Tomoki, you can do it.</i>

18
00:00:43,843 --> 00:00:45,978
<i>- Apply strong pressure to the wound.</i>
- Don't die.

19
00:00:45,979 --> 00:00:47,714
Don't die, Tatsuki.

20
00:01:15,642 --> 00:01:16,476
Tatsuki.

21
00:01:22,882 --> 00:01:23,783
Tatsuki.

22
00:01:28,721 --> 00:01:29,556
I'm sorry.

23
00:01:31,424 --> 00:01:32,725
Tomoki.

24
00:01:36,162 --> 00:01:37,330
I'm so glad

25
00:01:38,465 --> 00:01:39,666
you're alive.

26
00:01:52,912 --> 00:01:53,980
Tomoki.

27
00:01:54,681 --> 00:01:55,914
How's Mr. Tatsuki?

28
00:01:55,915 --> 00:01:57,183
Is he all right?

29
00:02:02,789 --> 00:02:04,924
Why are you here?

30
00:02:07,694 --> 00:02:08,928
I left

31
00:02:09,696 --> 00:02:11,364
my teaching job at middle school,

32
00:02:11,865 --> 00:02:15,268
and now I'm working at Yukanai.

33
00:02:19,305 --> 00:02:20,473
I see.

34
00:02:22,242 --> 00:02:23,510
I had no idea.

35
00:02:26,045 --> 00:02:30,083
I also had no idea you were Tomoki,
my former student, even though

36
00:02:31,451 --> 00:02:33,019
I even went to your house.

37
00:02:38,391 --> 00:02:39,659
I'm sorry.

38
00:02:42,829 --> 00:02:43,963
For what?

39
00:02:48,768 --> 00:02:50,470
You were being bullied,

40
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:54,407
and had to transfer schools
because of that

41
00:02:56,242 --> 00:02:57,677
but I failed to notice anything

42
00:03:00,246 --> 00:03:02,015
even though I was your homeroom teacher.

43
00:03:06,653 --> 00:03:08,221
It's too late for apologies now.

44
00:03:11,824 --> 00:03:13,193
You're right.

45
00:03:16,296 --> 00:03:17,163
I'm

46
00:03:19,866 --> 00:03:21,301
the worst.

47
00:03:22,702 --> 00:03:23,536
What?

48
00:03:24,370 --> 00:03:25,672
I was bullied,

49
00:03:29,042 --> 00:03:30,210
transferred schools,

50
00:03:33,546 --> 00:03:35,048
stopped going to school…

51
00:03:40,119 --> 00:03:41,921
dragged Tatsuki into it,

52
00:03:45,458 --> 00:03:46,793
and almost killed him.

53
00:03:50,530 --> 00:03:51,764
I'm

54
00:03:57,904 --> 00:03:58,938
worse than trash.

55
00:04:00,406 --> 00:04:03,610
That's not true.
Everything's going to be all right.

56
00:04:06,980 --> 00:04:08,248
It's going to be all right?

57
00:04:09,682 --> 00:04:10,516
What do you mean?

58
00:04:12,051 --> 00:04:13,052
Tell me,

59
00:04:16,356 --> 00:04:18,291
what does the future hold for me?

60
00:04:20,460 --> 00:04:22,495
I'm already facing setbacks,

61
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:25,598
so how am I

62
00:04:28,801 --> 00:04:30,770
supposed to live from now on?

63
00:04:49,922 --> 00:04:53,026
FORGET IT.
YOU HAVEN'T CHANGED AT ALL

64
00:05:10,076 --> 00:05:10,976
YUKANAI

65
00:05:10,977 --> 00:05:14,681
Mr. Tatsuki will be hospitalized
for about a week.

66
00:05:15,848 --> 00:05:19,786
When I heard that he fell,
I almost had a heart attack.

67
00:05:20,853 --> 00:05:22,255
He'll be okay, right?

68
00:05:23,556 --> 00:05:26,558
He said he's sorry
for making everyone worry.

69
00:05:26,559 --> 00:05:28,795
We have to work extra hard
in Tatsuki's place.

70
00:05:29,996 --> 00:05:32,565
If there's anything I can do to help,
let me know.

71
00:05:33,966 --> 00:05:34,801
Thank you.

72
00:05:35,868 --> 00:05:38,004
Then can you help me wash the muddy boots?

73
00:05:38,671 --> 00:05:39,505
What?

74
00:05:40,206 --> 00:05:41,040
- Uh, sure.
- Wait.

75
00:05:41,574 --> 00:05:42,408
Show more enthusiasm.

76
00:05:43,242 --> 00:05:44,643
- I mean, I'll do it!
- Come on.

77
00:05:44,644 --> 00:05:46,211
I'll do it. My pleasure.

78
00:05:46,212 --> 00:05:48,147
- Let's get to it.
- Yes, let's.

79
00:05:49,048 --> 00:05:50,216
<i>Worse than trash, huh?</i>

80
00:05:50,717 --> 00:05:53,119
He sounded like he had
given up on everything.

81
00:05:54,387 --> 00:05:56,356
What should we do?

82
00:06:00,893 --> 00:06:01,728
<i>Palxion</i>.

83
00:06:03,029 --> 00:06:04,963
- The game?
- Yeah.

84
00:06:04,964 --> 00:06:09,035
- I've never played it before…
- I'll introduce you to a good teacher.

85
00:06:13,406 --> 00:06:14,673
Teacher Tonetaku,

86
00:06:14,674 --> 00:06:16,309
please help me out.

87
00:06:17,343 --> 00:06:19,112
I'm studying for my entrance exam,
you know.

88
00:06:19,612 --> 00:06:22,315
I'm sorry.
I'll help you with your studies later on.

89
00:06:25,251 --> 00:06:28,053
But I heard that Tomoki
deleted his account.

90
00:06:28,054 --> 00:06:30,655
Does that mean he's no longer
playing the game?

91
00:06:30,656 --> 00:06:31,656
Well,

92
00:06:31,657 --> 00:06:34,693
he might be playing
under a different name.

93
00:06:34,694 --> 00:06:35,994
More importantly,

94
00:06:35,995 --> 00:06:37,429
you're using your real name?

95
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:38,363
Why?

96
00:06:38,364 --> 00:06:39,332
Is that weird?

97
00:06:39,832 --> 00:06:40,766
No, it's fine.

98
00:06:40,767 --> 00:06:44,137
I have no idea what I'm supposed to do.

99
00:06:44,704 --> 00:06:46,872
First, defeat enemies

100
00:06:46,873 --> 00:06:49,141
to collect weapons and items,

101
00:06:49,142 --> 00:06:50,041
and boost your stats.

102
00:06:50,042 --> 00:06:51,943
Stats? Okay.

103
00:06:51,944 --> 00:06:55,280
Even if you find Tomoki, he won't
let you join his team if you're weak.

104
00:06:55,281 --> 00:06:58,984
Right, because I can't speak with him
unless we become a team.

105
00:06:58,985 --> 00:06:59,986
That's right.

106
00:07:00,887 --> 00:07:02,455
What's this? Is it an apple?

107
00:07:02,955 --> 00:07:05,424
- What?
- But it only restores you a tiny bit,

108
00:07:05,425 --> 00:07:07,092
and it becomes extra baggage,

109
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:09,728
- so you can just ignore it.
- But apples are so delicious.

110
00:07:09,729 --> 00:07:11,463
How do I take it?

111
00:07:11,464 --> 00:07:12,597
Wait… What's going on?

112
00:07:12,598 --> 00:07:14,299
What? What happened?

113
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:15,333
What happened?

114
00:07:15,334 --> 00:07:16,869
- Why?
- It's a long road ahead of us.

115
00:07:25,044 --> 00:07:28,281
AOMINESHIZUKU

116
00:07:28,948 --> 00:07:29,848
Shi-chan.

117
00:07:29,849 --> 00:07:32,050
Let's play a card game.

118
00:07:32,051 --> 00:07:34,920
Sorry Kae-chan,
I'm a little busy right now.

119
00:07:34,921 --> 00:07:36,656
When will you be done with that?

120
00:07:38,257 --> 00:07:39,492
Sakurako and Kae-chan.

121
00:07:40,059 --> 00:07:42,160
- Can I join you guys instead?
- Sure.

122
00:07:42,161 --> 00:07:44,030
- Let's go.
- All right, let's play.

123
00:07:47,066 --> 00:07:48,167
All right.

124
00:07:48,901 --> 00:07:50,870
Let's see…

125
00:07:52,038 --> 00:07:53,038
Look at this.

126
00:07:53,039 --> 00:07:55,842
- What is it?
- Let's play this.

127
00:07:56,976 --> 00:07:58,144
It's an apple.

128
00:08:15,962 --> 00:08:17,630
PAYPHONE

129
00:08:24,670 --> 00:08:26,606
Hello?

130
00:08:27,473 --> 00:08:28,307
It's Tatsuki.

131
00:08:30,409 --> 00:08:31,944
Why are you using the payphone?

132
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:33,913
My phone ran out of battery.

133
00:08:34,847 --> 00:08:36,649
<i>I'll bring you a charger next time.</i>

134
00:08:38,718 --> 00:08:40,019
Did you find Tomoki?

135
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,722
Not yet.

136
00:08:43,356 --> 00:08:45,057
I forgot to mention this before, but…

137
00:08:45,558 --> 00:08:46,826
What is it?

138
00:08:47,994 --> 00:08:50,496
Tomoki will only show up at District 18.

139
00:08:52,798 --> 00:08:55,734
You should've told me that sooner!

140
00:08:55,735 --> 00:08:58,370
I've been playing
in a completely different area!

141
00:08:58,371 --> 00:08:59,205
<i>Sorry.</i>

142
00:09:00,273 --> 00:09:01,173
Um…

143
00:09:01,741 --> 00:09:04,876
is it really better to search for Tomoki
within the game

144
00:09:04,877 --> 00:09:08,414
rather than going directly to his house?

145
00:09:10,716 --> 00:09:12,852
I'm sure he'll go back
to playing that game again.

146
00:09:14,186 --> 00:09:15,388
I understand.

147
00:09:16,556 --> 00:09:19,791
By the way, how's your injury?

148
00:09:19,792 --> 00:09:21,360
<i>- Oh no, I'm out of coins.</i>
- What?

149
00:09:35,641 --> 00:09:36,475
What should we do?

150
00:09:37,777 --> 00:09:38,743
Should we wake her up?

151
00:09:38,744 --> 00:09:41,747
Hey, hold on.
Let her sleep a little longer.

152
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:43,683
Want to make some pancakes?

153
00:09:44,483 --> 00:09:45,918
- Pancakes?
- Really?

154
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:49,154
- Shh, quiet.
- Let's go.

155
00:09:49,155 --> 00:09:50,822
And then?

156
00:09:50,823 --> 00:09:52,857
- Keep going.
- Keep going?

157
00:09:52,858 --> 00:09:55,026
And this is… hold on…

158
00:09:55,027 --> 00:09:56,328
- What? Huh?
- That's the wall.

159
00:09:56,329 --> 00:09:57,796
You're rubbing against the wall.

160
00:09:57,797 --> 00:09:59,130
- Step away.
- How did that happen?

161
00:09:59,131 --> 00:10:00,066
- Step away.
- I am.

162
00:10:11,243 --> 00:10:12,612
Yanatomo…

163
00:10:13,312 --> 00:10:14,981
Tomoki Yanagisawa…

164
00:10:17,650 --> 00:10:19,585
Is that Tomoki? What am I supposed to do?

165
00:10:20,152 --> 00:10:21,886
I have to become his friend.

166
00:10:21,887 --> 00:10:23,089
Let's see.

167
00:10:23,589 --> 00:10:25,390
SEND FRIEND REQUEST TO YANATOMO444

168
00:10:25,391 --> 00:10:26,625
SEND

169
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:29,294
Tomoki, please accept my friend request!

170
00:10:29,295 --> 00:10:31,162
FRIEND REQUEST WAS SENT TO YANATOMO444

171
00:10:31,163 --> 00:10:32,130
YANATOMO444 DENIED THE FRIEND REQUEST

172
00:10:32,131 --> 00:10:34,233
DENIED THE FRIEND REQUEST

173
00:10:35,067 --> 00:10:36,202
He didn't accept?

174
00:10:38,871 --> 00:10:39,872
Let's do it again.

175
00:10:41,007 --> 00:10:42,540
SEND FRIEND REQUEST TO YANATOMO444

176
00:10:42,541 --> 00:10:45,611
Please, please accept it.

177
00:10:46,979 --> 00:10:48,214
YOU HAVE BEEN BLOCKED BY YANATOMO444

178
00:10:51,884 --> 00:10:55,021
He blocked me…

179
00:10:58,290 --> 00:10:59,992
YUKANAI

180
00:11:03,295 --> 00:11:05,096
Good morning.

181
00:11:05,097 --> 00:11:06,565
It's Tatsuki.

182
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:08,334
- You're okay now?
- Yup.

183
00:11:09,068 --> 00:11:10,369
Tatsuki.

184
00:11:11,303 --> 00:11:15,007
When you were gone,
I was about to die of loneliness.

185
00:11:15,741 --> 00:11:17,008
Sorry I was away for so long.

186
00:11:17,009 --> 00:11:18,309
Can you run?

187
00:11:18,310 --> 00:11:20,179
- Let's play tag.
- Freeze tag.

188
00:11:20,746 --> 00:11:22,514
- I don't think I can run yet.
- Let's do it…

189
00:11:22,515 --> 00:11:23,848
Where does it hurt?

190
00:11:23,849 --> 00:11:26,184
- Here?
- Stop that.

191
00:11:26,185 --> 00:11:27,787
- You can't do that.
- Tatsuki.

192
00:11:28,521 --> 00:11:30,456
Welcome back.

193
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:33,125
Sorry I was gone for so long.

194
00:11:33,626 --> 00:11:36,394
It was easier for us
with one less child to look after.

195
00:11:36,395 --> 00:11:37,529
Hey!

196
00:11:37,530 --> 00:11:38,830
She's right.

197
00:11:38,831 --> 00:11:40,865
Who're you calling a kid?
Don't agree with her!

198
00:11:40,866 --> 00:11:42,301
Mr. Tatsuki.

199
00:11:43,135 --> 00:11:44,302
Hello.

200
00:11:44,303 --> 00:11:45,137
How's Tomoki?

201
00:11:46,372 --> 00:11:47,572
I'm sorry,

202
00:11:47,573 --> 00:11:49,641
but he ended up blocking me.

203
00:11:49,642 --> 00:11:51,143
I see.

204
00:11:53,045 --> 00:11:54,113
- Whoa.
- Hey.

205
00:11:54,814 --> 00:11:56,916
- Are you all right?
- Sorry.

206
00:12:00,052 --> 00:12:01,954
She hasn't been getting enough sleep?

207
00:12:02,722 --> 00:12:04,690
That's part of it too…

208
00:12:07,326 --> 00:12:09,295
I'm sorry I couldn't be of any help.

209
00:12:11,897 --> 00:12:14,100
No matter what I do,
I can't seem to get it right.

210
00:12:15,801 --> 00:12:17,536
You're feeling a little down, aren't you?

211
00:12:18,037 --> 00:12:20,872
Let's start by getting good rest

212
00:12:20,873 --> 00:12:21,707
and eating well.

213
00:12:23,042 --> 00:12:24,210
I'm sorry.

214
00:12:30,716 --> 00:12:31,717
Hey.

215
00:12:33,586 --> 00:12:35,087
I'm glad you got discharged.

216
00:12:35,821 --> 00:12:37,188
Sorry for making you worry.

217
00:12:37,189 --> 00:12:38,224
No problem at all.

218
00:12:39,859 --> 00:12:41,727
- Are you all right now?
- Yes.

219
00:12:42,361 --> 00:12:45,297
I'm more worried
about Ms. Shizuku right now.

220
00:12:45,865 --> 00:12:48,968
- Why?
- I think it's related to Tomoki.

221
00:12:49,535 --> 00:12:52,036
<i>She used to be his homeroom teacher,</i>

222
00:12:52,037 --> 00:12:55,306
<i>but I think she's feeling responsible
for everything that happened.</i>

223
00:12:55,307 --> 00:12:57,042
I can see that.

224
00:12:58,010 --> 00:12:59,845
Plus, while I was hospitalized,

225
00:13:00,346 --> 00:13:02,815
I asked her to find Tomoki within <i>Palxion</i>.

226
00:13:03,315 --> 00:13:04,682
I think she pushed herself too hard.

227
00:13:04,683 --> 00:13:07,685
She's not the type
who's very good with online games.

228
00:13:07,686 --> 00:13:09,789
Yeah, but…

229
00:13:11,891 --> 00:13:14,527
Right now, I think the only person
who can save Tomoki

230
00:13:15,261 --> 00:13:18,496
might be Ms. Shizuku who has
her own experience with school refusal.

231
00:13:18,497 --> 00:13:19,765
I…

232
00:13:20,399 --> 00:13:23,002
didn't go to school for six years
starting in middle school.

233
00:13:23,502 --> 00:13:26,304
So I think I understand
the feelings of kids

234
00:13:26,305 --> 00:13:28,040
experiencing school refusal.

235
00:13:31,043 --> 00:13:34,680
But at the same time, that would mean
having to confront her own past…

236
00:13:35,181 --> 00:13:36,482
so it’s a lot to ask of her.

237
00:13:37,383 --> 00:13:38,250
Yes.

238
00:13:40,419 --> 00:13:42,488
So, in order to help Tomoki,

239
00:13:43,155 --> 00:13:46,559
the first thing you need to do
is empathize with Shi-chan's feelings.

240
00:13:47,426 --> 00:13:48,527
Empathize?

241
00:13:51,130 --> 00:13:52,198
I have a good idea.

242
00:14:05,244 --> 00:14:07,579
I'm sorry about earlier.

243
00:14:07,580 --> 00:14:09,013
You're okay now?

244
00:14:09,014 --> 00:14:11,282
Yes, I feel a lot better now.

245
00:14:11,283 --> 00:14:12,251
I'm glad.

246
00:14:14,253 --> 00:14:15,421
What's this?

247
00:14:16,322 --> 00:14:19,158
I had an idea to narrate our life story
using the <i>kamishibai</i> format.

248
00:14:19,758 --> 00:14:20,659
<i>Kamishibai</i>?

249
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:23,762
Do you want to give it a try?

250
00:14:24,430 --> 00:14:26,799
- Me?
- Let's do it together.

251
00:14:31,704 --> 00:14:33,606
To start with,

252
00:14:34,940 --> 00:14:36,507
how would you express

253
00:14:36,508 --> 00:14:38,510
your elementary school days
in a single picture?

254
00:14:40,646 --> 00:14:43,249
My elementary school days?

255
00:14:43,983 --> 00:14:47,085
This approach uses
the concept of "life scenarios"

256
00:14:47,086 --> 00:14:48,920
to reflect upon one's past,

257
00:14:48,921 --> 00:14:51,490
serving as a way to once again
confront and face oneself.

258
00:14:53,359 --> 00:14:54,927
Let's give it a try.

259
00:14:55,427 --> 00:14:56,262
Okay.

260
00:14:56,762 --> 00:14:58,063
I'll start first.

261
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:01,700
Okay, let's see…

262
00:15:15,247 --> 00:15:17,616
It's very systematic and precise.

263
00:15:18,684 --> 00:15:20,953
Back in elementary school,
I was actually very meticulous.

264
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:22,721
I was a role model student.

265
00:15:23,222 --> 00:15:24,290
I see.

266
00:15:28,594 --> 00:15:30,296
I was…

267
00:15:30,796 --> 00:15:32,530
Who knows what comes next?

268
00:15:32,531 --> 00:15:34,065
- Me!
- Me!

269
00:15:34,066 --> 00:15:35,967
- Aomine.
- Yes.

270
00:15:35,968 --> 00:15:37,669
<i>I liked studying,</i>

271
00:15:37,670 --> 00:15:40,138
<i>and I had lots of friends too,</i>

272
00:15:40,139 --> 00:15:42,073
<i>so I loved going to school.</i>

273
00:15:42,074 --> 00:15:44,209
Go, Shi-chan!

274
00:15:49,415 --> 00:15:51,850
I was having a blast every day.

275
00:15:53,786 --> 00:15:54,686
That's nice.

276
00:15:54,687 --> 00:15:55,521
Yes.

277
00:15:59,258 --> 00:16:02,895
Now let's move onto middle school.

278
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:11,070
Middle school days…

279
00:16:24,083 --> 00:16:25,584
That was fast.

280
00:16:27,519 --> 00:16:30,489
I only remember studying
during middle school.

281
00:16:35,527 --> 00:16:37,262
During middle school…

282
00:16:37,896 --> 00:16:40,933
Does anyone know which preposition
goes in the parentheses?

283
00:16:41,433 --> 00:16:42,267
Yes.

284
00:16:42,768 --> 00:16:43,802
Aomine.

285
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:45,837
It's "before."

286
00:16:45,838 --> 00:16:48,873
- You're speaking like a native.
- Great accent.

287
00:16:48,874 --> 00:16:52,544
- Quiet, everyone.
- Impressive accent.

288
00:16:57,116 --> 00:16:59,151
<i>When I started middle school…</i>

289
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,321
Thanks for waiting.

290
00:17:04,556 --> 00:17:05,391
Sorry.

291
00:17:05,991 --> 00:17:08,794
<i>People began to ignore me…</i>

292
00:17:12,264 --> 00:17:13,332
<i>And so,</i>

293
00:17:15,501 --> 00:17:18,037
<i>it gradually became difficult
for me to leave my room.</i>

294
00:17:22,808 --> 00:17:24,443
Everything in front of me

295
00:17:26,445 --> 00:17:27,813
was in complete darkness.

296
00:17:37,256 --> 00:17:40,259
How about after you graduated
middle school?

297
00:17:41,293 --> 00:17:42,294
Okay.

298
00:17:42,861 --> 00:17:45,197
But I didn't go to high school.

299
00:18:14,226 --> 00:18:16,061
What made you decide

300
00:18:17,029 --> 00:18:19,531
to escape the complete darkness?

301
00:18:23,902 --> 00:18:25,471
I happened to stumble across

302
00:18:26,605 --> 00:18:29,440
the social media of the person
who used to bully me

303
00:18:29,441 --> 00:18:31,143
back in middle school.

304
00:18:34,746 --> 00:18:38,417
<i>I had spent years
holed up in a dim, gloomy room.</i>

305
00:18:39,685 --> 00:18:43,589
<i>Yet, there she was,
living her best life ever.</i>

306
00:18:45,324 --> 00:18:46,291
<i>When I thought about</i>

307
00:18:46,792 --> 00:18:50,162
<i>just how unfair the world is,</i>

308
00:18:52,231 --> 00:18:53,632
a surge of frustration

309
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:56,802
and anger welled up inside me.

310
00:18:58,036 --> 00:19:01,039
So you got your
high school equivalency diploma?

311
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:02,474
Yes.

312
00:19:03,275 --> 00:19:06,011
I was determined to rise above them.

313
00:19:13,418 --> 00:19:15,554
How about after you became a teacher?

314
00:19:22,194 --> 00:19:24,629
After I became a teacher…

315
00:19:24,630 --> 00:19:27,699
First, let's look at auxiliary verbs
that have four meanings.

316
00:19:28,834 --> 00:19:31,536
"Ru," "raru."

317
00:19:31,537 --> 00:19:32,737
"Ru" is

318
00:19:32,738 --> 00:19:35,840
"re," "re," "ru," "ruru"…

319
00:19:35,841 --> 00:19:40,179
Ruru, ole, ole, ole…

320
00:19:42,481 --> 00:19:44,415
Quiet down, everyone.

321
00:19:44,416 --> 00:19:47,519
Why is my child failing language arts?

322
00:19:48,554 --> 00:19:50,521
- That's because…
- First of all,

323
00:19:50,522 --> 00:19:53,125
everyone's complaining about
the poor quality of your curriculum.

324
00:19:54,059 --> 00:19:57,262
Maybe you're not qualified
to be a teacher.

325
00:19:57,829 --> 00:20:00,599
The children's future is on the line here!

326
00:20:01,967 --> 00:20:03,235
I'm sorry.

327
00:20:10,142 --> 00:20:12,244
<i>It was the job I always dreamed of.</i>

328
00:20:14,913 --> 00:20:17,549
<i>Yet it wasn't going
the way I expected it to.</i>

329
00:20:20,185 --> 00:20:22,120
<i>Back when I was in middle school,</i>

330
00:20:23,589 --> 00:20:27,159
<i>I wanted the people around me
to notice how much I was suffering,</i>

331
00:20:28,427 --> 00:20:30,095
<i>but after I became a teacher,</i>

332
00:20:34,266 --> 00:20:38,070
I failed to pick up
on my students’ cries for help…

333
00:20:47,346 --> 00:20:49,915
I turned into the kind of adult
I swore I would never become.

334
00:20:58,824 --> 00:20:59,825
Then

335
00:21:02,661 --> 00:21:03,629
if you had the chance

336
00:21:04,229 --> 00:21:06,732
to rewrite your "life scenario,"

337
00:21:09,001 --> 00:21:10,235
how would it have played out?

338
00:21:12,638 --> 00:21:14,206
If you hadn't

339
00:21:15,540 --> 00:21:18,143
been bullied during middle school,

340
00:21:19,344 --> 00:21:20,812
what do you think

341
00:21:21,580 --> 00:21:23,015
your life would've been like?

342
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:28,887
I'm sure I would have gone
on to high school and then university.

343
00:21:33,525 --> 00:21:35,193
What about after that?

344
00:21:46,038 --> 00:21:47,839
After that…

345
00:22:24,376 --> 00:22:26,545
It's vibrant.

346
00:22:32,050 --> 00:22:33,018
I think

347
00:22:33,518 --> 00:22:36,021
I would have still dreamed
of becoming a teacher.

348
00:22:37,956 --> 00:22:40,425
But I would've had more self-confidence,

349
00:22:42,060 --> 00:22:44,363
and would've been popular
with the students…

350
00:22:46,798 --> 00:22:50,469
I imagine it would have been
a future filled with laughter and joy.

351
00:22:54,439 --> 00:22:56,274
But going through school refusal

352
00:22:59,144 --> 00:23:01,313
robbed me of so many things.

353
00:23:07,285 --> 00:23:09,721
How about now?

354
00:23:24,236 --> 00:23:26,271
- You're too good at this.
- Sorry about that.

355
00:23:30,208 --> 00:23:31,743
Well…

356
00:23:34,646 --> 00:23:36,047
I'm not sure.

357
00:23:49,127 --> 00:23:51,797
You drew trees too?

358
00:23:53,598 --> 00:23:54,466
‎Yeah.

359
00:23:56,401 --> 00:24:00,772
Right now, my family and I are
living apart and it’s entirely my fault…

360
00:24:03,408 --> 00:24:07,112
But if I could rewrite my "life scenario,"

361
00:24:08,413 --> 00:24:09,681
I wonder if the three of us

362
00:24:10,449 --> 00:24:12,083
<i>would be living together right now.</i>

363
00:24:17,422 --> 00:24:20,725
Are you still in contact with your family?

364
00:24:22,260 --> 00:24:26,530
We had promised to meet and talk
for the first time in a while,

365
00:24:26,531 --> 00:24:29,634
but then that thing with Tomoki happened,
so I couldn't go.

366
00:24:31,770 --> 00:24:34,172
Did you explain why you couldn't go?

367
00:24:36,475 --> 00:24:37,309
No.

368
00:24:40,579 --> 00:24:43,982
I'm sure she'll understand if you
talk to her and explain what happened.

369
00:24:53,158 --> 00:24:54,493
Ms. Shizuku,

370
00:24:55,460 --> 00:24:57,696
you shouldn't give up
on talking with Tomoki either.

371
00:25:00,398 --> 00:25:02,766
I believe that your personal experience

372
00:25:02,767 --> 00:25:04,002
will surely

373
00:25:05,804 --> 00:25:07,706
resonate with Tomoki.

374
00:25:12,210 --> 00:25:13,044
Okay.

375
00:25:16,982 --> 00:25:19,083
AOMINESHIZUKU

376
00:25:19,084 --> 00:25:20,784
You haven't leveled up at all!

377
00:25:20,785 --> 00:25:23,721
Because everyone attacks me
the moment they see me.

378
00:25:23,722 --> 00:25:25,790
That's what this game is about.

379
00:25:27,192 --> 00:25:30,461
And why are you collecting so many apples?

380
00:25:30,462 --> 00:25:32,130
I'm very good at finding apples.

381
00:25:35,233 --> 00:25:37,902
You found someone who you think
is Tomoki, right?

382
00:25:37,903 --> 00:25:39,937
Yes, the username was "yanatomo."

383
00:25:39,938 --> 00:25:42,172
So I sent a friend request,

384
00:25:42,173 --> 00:25:43,708
but I got blocked.

385
00:25:46,044 --> 00:25:46,945
What should we do?

386
00:25:48,446 --> 00:25:49,580
Hey.

387
00:25:49,581 --> 00:25:51,682
<i>Palxion</i> is holding an event.

388
00:25:51,683 --> 00:25:53,051
Why don't you guys go?

389
00:25:53,552 --> 00:25:54,752
Beach cleanup?

390
00:25:54,753 --> 00:25:57,087
Everyone is going to pick up trash
at the beach together,

391
00:25:57,088 --> 00:25:58,623
and hold a <i>Palxion</i> tournament after that.

392
00:25:59,925 --> 00:26:00,824
That sounds fun.

393
00:26:00,825 --> 00:26:03,761
You have to enter in teams of five.

394
00:26:03,762 --> 00:26:05,630
Tatsuki and Shi-chan makes two.

395
00:26:06,665 --> 00:26:09,800
Even if Tomoki agrees to join you guys,
you'll still need

396
00:26:09,801 --> 00:26:10,768
two more people.

397
00:26:10,769 --> 00:26:11,869
What about you?

398
00:26:11,870 --> 00:26:13,604
Sorry, I have my mock exam that day.

399
00:26:13,605 --> 00:26:15,040
Okay.

400
00:26:17,042 --> 00:26:18,709
I have somewhere to go.

401
00:26:18,710 --> 00:26:19,710
Excuse me.

402
00:26:19,711 --> 00:26:20,845
Hey.

403
00:26:23,248 --> 00:26:26,184
Funamori, Iino, thanks for agreeing
to my sudden request.

404
00:26:26,851 --> 00:26:30,421
We haven't seen Tomoki in the game
ever since that day, so we don't know

405
00:26:30,422 --> 00:26:32,090
if he'll accept
our invitation to the event.

406
00:26:32,824 --> 00:26:33,959
Yeah…

407
00:26:35,694 --> 00:26:39,230
That's why I have no choice
but to do things the old-fashioned way.

408
00:26:41,766 --> 00:26:42,800
Hello.

409
00:26:42,801 --> 00:26:44,536
Sorry for coming all of a sudden.

410
00:26:45,036 --> 00:26:46,605
Is Tomoki home?

411
00:26:47,238 --> 00:26:48,606
He's in his room.

412
00:26:48,607 --> 00:26:50,575
He hasn't come out since that incident.

413
00:26:51,376 --> 00:26:52,611
I see.

414
00:26:53,111 --> 00:26:54,946
- Please come inside.
- Thank you.

415
00:26:57,048 --> 00:26:58,216
Tomoki.

416
00:26:58,883 --> 00:27:01,953
Ms. Aomine and your friends are here.

417
00:27:10,295 --> 00:27:12,330
I'm sorry for coming all of a sudden.

418
00:27:14,332 --> 00:27:17,469
Mr. Tatsuki
was discharged from the hospital.

419
00:27:22,007 --> 00:27:24,376
I started playing <i>Palxion</i> too.

420
00:27:25,410 --> 00:27:27,811
I’ve been running around
District 18 every day,

421
00:27:27,812 --> 00:27:30,615
hoping I might run into you.

422
00:27:31,116 --> 00:27:34,585
But I just keep getting lost,
and I get shot down almost immediately.

423
00:27:34,586 --> 00:27:35,920
That game is really tough.

424
00:27:41,292 --> 00:27:44,496
You know about the event coming up
hosted by <i>Palxion</i>, right?

425
00:27:45,030 --> 00:27:47,832
Would you please join our team?

426
00:27:53,138 --> 00:27:55,540
We have to enter as a team of five

427
00:27:56,041 --> 00:27:57,575
and we really need your help, Tomoki.

428
00:27:58,176 --> 00:28:02,146
I heard that the winner
gets a golden artifact.

429
00:28:02,147 --> 00:28:03,214
Isn't that insane?

430
00:28:12,457 --> 00:28:14,759
Sorry to have bothered you.
We'll be going now.

431
00:28:15,593 --> 00:28:19,164
If you have the chance,
please visit the church in District 18.

432
00:28:28,106 --> 00:28:31,642
If Tomoki shows up, I'll use my account
to invite him to my party,

433
00:28:31,643 --> 00:28:32,677
so you can go home now.

434
00:28:33,178 --> 00:28:35,279
But I have to do this one thing every day,

435
00:28:35,280 --> 00:28:36,581
so just let me finish it…

436
00:28:37,282 --> 00:28:40,351
- Okay, let's see…
- Um…

437
00:28:41,252 --> 00:28:43,455
If you exhaust yourself,
you won't be able to join the event.

438
00:28:45,023 --> 00:28:45,857
Okay, I'll go home.

439
00:28:46,491 --> 00:28:49,093
I'll be going now.

440
00:28:49,094 --> 00:28:50,228
Bye.

441
00:29:00,739 --> 00:29:03,207
YANATOMO444

442
00:29:03,208 --> 00:29:04,342
DISTRICT 18

443
00:29:14,652 --> 00:29:18,423
<i>If you have the chance,
please visit the church in District 18.</i>

444
00:29:31,669 --> 00:29:33,037
Why are there so many apples?

445
00:29:44,482 --> 00:29:46,284
‎APPLE - 3 RECOVERY POINTS

446
00:30:05,637 --> 00:30:07,872
BEACH CLEANUP

447
00:30:08,540 --> 00:30:10,140
Wow,

448
00:30:10,141 --> 00:30:11,976
it's been so long
since I came to the beach.

449
00:30:14,579 --> 00:30:15,580
Tomoki?

450
00:30:19,617 --> 00:30:20,819
Tomoki!

451
00:30:21,452 --> 00:30:22,487
Tomoki!

452
00:30:24,889 --> 00:30:26,523
It's been a while.

453
00:30:26,524 --> 00:30:27,959
Long time no see.

454
00:30:30,662 --> 00:30:31,562
Tomoki.

455
00:30:31,563 --> 00:30:35,032
Thank you for joining us today
for the Beach Cleanup with <i>Palxion</i>!

456
00:30:35,033 --> 00:30:35,900
We appreciate it!

457
00:30:36,868 --> 00:30:38,836
The winning team

458
00:30:38,837 --> 00:30:41,305
will be awarded a golden artifact!

459
00:30:41,306 --> 00:30:42,307
No way!

460
00:30:54,285 --> 00:30:56,087
You're all right now?

461
00:30:58,056 --> 00:30:59,557
Yeah, I have great regenerative power.

462
00:31:02,961 --> 00:31:03,795
I'm sorry.

463
00:31:05,096 --> 00:31:06,797
You don't have to apologize.

464
00:31:06,798 --> 00:31:08,666
That was my own fault.

465
00:31:17,275 --> 00:31:18,877
Oh, this sea glass is nice.

466
00:31:30,922 --> 00:31:32,590
I wonder if even pretty seashells

467
00:31:33,291 --> 00:31:36,628
are just trash
because they've been discarded.

468
00:31:44,903 --> 00:31:46,037
Tomoki.

469
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:50,675
Ms. Shizuku

470
00:31:51,943 --> 00:31:54,012
says she wants to talk to you
about something.

471
00:32:02,820 --> 00:32:05,356
Thank you for unblocking me.

472
00:32:09,460 --> 00:32:11,329
What was up with all those apples?

473
00:32:13,831 --> 00:32:16,199
I was told to get stronger and level up,

474
00:32:16,200 --> 00:32:18,569
but all I can really do is collect apples.

475
00:32:24,709 --> 00:32:25,710
It's not that

476
00:32:28,079 --> 00:32:30,581
I have a grudge against you or anything,

477
00:32:33,785 --> 00:32:34,886
so you can leave me alone.

478
00:32:38,423 --> 00:32:40,057
I can't leave you alone.

479
00:32:40,058 --> 00:32:41,192
Why?

480
00:32:41,826 --> 00:32:44,295
I'm not your responsibility anymore.

481
00:32:49,701 --> 00:32:51,002
You know,

482
00:32:52,337 --> 00:32:54,706
I experienced years of school refusal

483
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:57,075
because I was bullied in middle school.

484
00:33:02,480 --> 00:33:05,216
It was so painful
to even think about that time,

485
00:33:05,717 --> 00:33:08,152
so I kept it buried
deep in the back of my mind for so long,

486
00:33:09,187 --> 00:33:11,422
but recently,
I had an opportunity to look back on it.

487
00:33:13,491 --> 00:33:15,393
The bullying was painful,

488
00:33:16,427 --> 00:33:19,664
and I was furious at myself for not
being able to do anything about it.

489
00:33:21,466 --> 00:33:24,168
There’s no doubt
it’s a dark chapter in my past.

490
00:33:27,271 --> 00:33:31,142
But I felt like it'd be too frustrating
to let things end the way it was.

491
00:33:34,312 --> 00:33:35,313
Frustrating?

492
00:33:38,349 --> 00:33:43,121
So I decided to take another chance
at doing what I love,

493
00:33:44,422 --> 00:33:46,357
and aimed to become a school teacher.

494
00:33:49,827 --> 00:33:52,163
Even so, I made lots of mistakes

495
00:33:53,564 --> 00:33:55,466
and even quit my job at the school.

496
00:33:58,436 --> 00:33:59,270
But then

497
00:34:01,072 --> 00:34:03,041
I met everyone at Yukanai,

498
00:34:04,175 --> 00:34:05,943
and I got to do what I love.

499
00:34:07,545 --> 00:34:08,646
So now,

500
00:34:10,214 --> 00:34:12,950
I think I might actually be happy.

501
00:34:16,721 --> 00:34:18,255
That said,

502
00:34:18,256 --> 00:34:21,325
I certainly don't think,
"I'm glad I went through school refusal."

503
00:34:22,960 --> 00:34:25,229
It would've been better
if the bullying had never happened,

504
00:34:26,464 --> 00:34:28,499
and I have no intention
of forgiving them either.

505
00:34:30,301 --> 00:34:31,169
But…

506
00:34:33,037 --> 00:34:33,971
But

507
00:34:36,274 --> 00:34:38,109
the past is the past.

508
00:34:39,811 --> 00:34:41,479
I want you

509
00:34:42,914 --> 00:34:46,884
to spend your time from now on
doing the things you love.

510
00:34:50,755 --> 00:34:52,190
Because isn't it frustrating?

511
00:34:53,458 --> 00:34:55,526
You didn't do anything wrong.

512
00:34:56,561 --> 00:35:00,131
So why do you have to think of yourself
as trash?

513
00:35:01,232 --> 00:35:02,266
That

514
00:35:04,102 --> 00:35:05,369
frustrates me.

515
00:35:16,147 --> 00:35:17,048
It's

516
00:35:20,818 --> 00:35:21,886
frustrating for me too.

517
00:35:30,461 --> 00:35:31,462
Then

518
00:35:33,898 --> 00:35:36,167
do what you love to your heart's content.

519
00:36:01,826 --> 00:36:03,660
Everyone picked up a lot of trash.

520
00:36:03,661 --> 00:36:05,897
There were lots of plastic bottles.

521
00:36:06,597 --> 00:36:07,765
And plastic wrappers.

522
00:36:08,332 --> 00:36:10,568
There's still some time before the battle,

523
00:36:11,602 --> 00:36:12,603
so let's make something.

524
00:36:13,804 --> 00:36:15,572
Junk art, beach edition?

525
00:36:15,573 --> 00:36:16,507
Yeah.

526
00:36:23,814 --> 00:36:26,250
- All right, all done.
- All right, all done.

527
00:36:37,695 --> 00:36:38,529
Done.

528
00:36:40,398 --> 00:36:41,598
That looks nice.

529
00:36:41,599 --> 00:36:42,999
It does, huh?

530
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:45,369
Lots of objects are neatly tucked
in between the spikes.

531
00:36:46,237 --> 00:36:49,740
This spiky part is kind of like me.

532
00:36:50,841 --> 00:36:51,776
I can see that.

533
00:36:52,643 --> 00:36:54,879
It can seem unapproachable at first,

534
00:36:55,479 --> 00:36:58,616
but it's surrounded
by a gentle atmosphere.

535
00:37:04,522 --> 00:37:06,590
Oh no! It's time for the battle!

536
00:37:06,591 --> 00:37:07,490
- What?
- On, no!

537
00:37:07,491 --> 00:37:08,758
- Oh, crap!
- Let's hurry.

538
00:37:08,759 --> 00:37:09,726
Run!

539
00:37:09,727 --> 00:37:10,627
Let's go.

540
00:37:10,628 --> 00:37:12,329
Hold on.

541
00:37:12,330 --> 00:37:13,897
- Be careful.
- Tomoki.

542
00:37:13,898 --> 00:37:15,099
It's going to fall.

543
00:37:15,733 --> 00:37:17,601
- Hold on.
- Hurry.

544
00:37:17,602 --> 00:37:18,569
Tomoki.

545
00:37:24,242 --> 00:37:26,309
- I'm back.
- Welcome back.

546
00:37:26,310 --> 00:37:27,778
You were out for a while.

547
00:37:30,548 --> 00:37:32,083
What is that?

548
00:37:32,583 --> 00:37:33,417
I made it at the beach.

549
00:37:34,418 --> 00:37:36,020
This isn't trash.

550
00:37:37,655 --> 00:37:39,090
It's beautiful.

551
00:37:40,558 --> 00:37:42,960
Go wash your hands so that we can eat.

552
00:37:44,161 --> 00:37:45,363
I'm hungry.

553
00:37:50,501 --> 00:37:51,501
You passed Kurumi.

554
00:37:51,502 --> 00:37:53,003
Go, go.

555
00:37:53,004 --> 00:37:55,706
For this, you go like this…

556
00:37:57,775 --> 00:37:58,908
Oh man,

557
00:37:58,909 --> 00:38:00,044
exams are such a drag.

558
00:38:00,611 --> 00:38:01,612
That's second grade level.

559
00:38:02,179 --> 00:38:03,246
Shut up.

560
00:38:03,247 --> 00:38:05,115
Let's work on it a little bit more.

561
00:38:05,116 --> 00:38:06,650
I can't, it's too hard.

562
00:38:06,651 --> 00:38:08,318
- You can do it.
- I want a different one.

563
00:38:08,319 --> 00:38:10,354
- Not this one.
- Okay, let's do a different one.

564
00:38:11,789 --> 00:38:13,891
Tomoki? Hey, it's Tomoki.

565
00:38:15,192 --> 00:38:17,395
Hello.

566
00:38:19,163 --> 00:38:20,131
Hello.

567
00:38:21,232 --> 00:38:23,000
- Hello.
- Hey.

568
00:38:23,768 --> 00:38:24,635
Hey.

569
00:38:26,070 --> 00:38:27,070
Wanna play <i>Mario Kart</i>?

570
00:38:27,071 --> 00:38:28,806
Tonetaku,
you were in the middle of studying.

571
00:38:29,373 --> 00:38:30,408
Shi-chan,

572
00:38:30,908 --> 00:38:34,544
we're already doomed, so it's pointless
to try any harder now.

573
00:38:34,545 --> 00:38:35,846
Come on…

574
00:38:37,882 --> 00:38:39,016
I've decided on my future path.

575
00:38:40,818 --> 00:38:42,819
- Really?
- You're kidding, right?

576
00:38:42,820 --> 00:38:46,056
I want to become an esports player,
so I decided

577
00:38:46,057 --> 00:38:47,624
to go to a vocational school.

578
00:38:47,625 --> 00:38:49,593
Is that right?

579
00:38:50,494 --> 00:38:51,395
Because

580
00:38:52,196 --> 00:38:54,832
you said that I should do what I love.

581
00:39:00,604 --> 00:39:01,772
That's a good plan.

582
00:39:04,308 --> 00:39:06,576
I thought about what I love enough
to give it my all,

583
00:39:06,577 --> 00:39:08,512
as if my life depended on it,

584
00:39:10,014 --> 00:39:10,948
and this was it.

585
00:39:12,183 --> 00:39:13,117
I see.

586
00:39:14,852 --> 00:39:16,320
I'm glad you found something.

587
00:39:18,122 --> 00:39:19,190
Shi-chan.

588
00:39:21,959 --> 00:39:23,260
You said

589
00:39:23,861 --> 00:39:27,365
that going through school refusal
was a dark chapter in your life,

590
00:39:30,301 --> 00:39:32,570
but to me, it's a heroic tale.

591
00:39:33,871 --> 00:39:35,005
Really?

592
00:39:35,673 --> 00:39:36,841
I'm glad

593
00:39:37,708 --> 00:39:39,443
you were my homeroom teacher, Shi-chan.

594
00:39:41,312 --> 00:39:42,246
Thank you.

595
00:39:45,850 --> 00:39:47,051
I'm grateful to you too.

596
00:39:48,252 --> 00:39:49,587
Thank you.

597
00:39:57,228 --> 00:39:59,329
<i>It seems like Tomoki is better now.</i>

598
00:39:59,330 --> 00:40:00,430
Yes.

599
00:40:00,431 --> 00:40:03,133
He even decided on what he wants to do
in the future.

600
00:40:03,134 --> 00:40:04,602
That's amazing.

601
00:40:05,136 --> 00:40:06,370
What did you say to help him?

602
00:40:08,272 --> 00:40:10,140
I told him to do what he loves

603
00:40:10,141 --> 00:40:12,209
to his heart's content.

604
00:40:12,877 --> 00:40:13,878
That's great advice.

605
00:40:15,946 --> 00:40:20,050
But I was able to regain that mindset

606
00:40:21,819 --> 00:40:23,521
thanks to Mr. Tatsuki.

607
00:40:24,722 --> 00:40:25,755
I see.

608
00:40:25,756 --> 00:40:27,658
But Mr. Tatsuki

609
00:40:28,192 --> 00:40:31,127
always prioritizes the children,

610
00:40:31,128 --> 00:40:34,931
and even flaked
on important appointments with his family,

611
00:40:34,932 --> 00:40:37,134
so I find myself worrying

612
00:40:37,635 --> 00:40:39,403
whether he's going to be okay.

613
00:40:40,571 --> 00:40:43,941
Maybe this time,
it's your turn to give him a little push.

614
00:40:45,376 --> 00:40:47,111
Me?

615
00:40:48,479 --> 00:40:50,247
Yes, in your own unique way.

616
00:40:54,018 --> 00:40:55,852
Shi-chan, let's go to the courtyard.

617
00:40:55,853 --> 00:40:56,986
Tatsuki is playing soccer.

618
00:40:56,987 --> 00:40:58,689
Run, Shi-chan.

619
00:40:59,190 --> 00:41:00,757
- Let's go, let's go.
- Bye.

620
00:41:00,758 --> 00:41:02,992
Okay, I'm coming.

621
00:41:02,993 --> 00:41:04,194
Okay, let's go.

622
00:41:04,195 --> 00:41:05,528
- All right.
- Hurry.

623
00:41:05,529 --> 00:41:08,432
- Hurry.
- I'm coming.

624
00:41:22,613 --> 00:41:23,848
Mr. Tatsuki.

625
00:41:25,049 --> 00:41:28,118
Have you been able to contact your family
after the recent incident?

626
00:41:29,687 --> 00:41:30,754
No.

627
00:41:31,689 --> 00:41:35,059
In that case, you’ll just remain
the terrible person who broke his promise.

628
00:41:36,393 --> 00:41:39,330
You really ought to have
a proper talk with them.

629
00:41:40,064 --> 00:41:41,632
Yeah, but…

630
00:41:42,800 --> 00:41:44,934
Can I borrow your phone for a bit?

631
00:41:44,935 --> 00:41:46,370
- What?
- Your phone.

632
00:41:47,638 --> 00:41:49,707
Sure…

633
00:41:50,274 --> 00:41:51,575
Thank you.

634
00:41:52,076 --> 00:41:53,577
Everyone,

635
00:41:54,078 --> 00:41:55,478
let's take a picture.

636
00:41:55,479 --> 00:41:56,747
Gather around.

637
00:41:57,715 --> 00:41:59,415
- I want to get in too.
- Okay.

638
00:41:59,416 --> 00:42:00,683
Okay, get in place.

639
00:42:00,684 --> 00:42:03,253
- Ready?
- Say,

640
00:42:03,254 --> 00:42:04,889
Yukanai.

641
00:42:05,890 --> 00:42:06,924
Thanks.

642
00:42:09,894 --> 00:42:11,060
Here.

643
00:42:11,061 --> 00:42:11,896
What was that for?

644
00:42:15,199 --> 00:42:16,734
Please send that to your wife.

645
00:42:17,535 --> 00:42:19,737
Tell her
that this is your current workplace.

646
00:42:20,304 --> 00:42:23,274
Ask her to come and see it sometime.

647
00:42:25,209 --> 00:42:26,443
Well…

648
00:42:28,212 --> 00:42:29,613
Please.

649
00:42:44,028 --> 00:42:46,029
I'M SORRY ABOUT THE OTHER DAY

650
00:42:46,030 --> 00:42:48,031
THIS IS WHERE I'M WORKING RIGHT NOW

651
00:42:48,032 --> 00:42:50,701
I'D LOVE FOR YOU TO COME BY
AND CHECK IT OUT SOMETIME

652
00:42:55,573 --> 00:42:57,508
YUKANAI

653
00:43:14,124 --> 00:43:15,225
Come in.

654
00:43:37,114 --> 00:43:41,986
We draw pictures and do arts and crafts
with the children here.

655
00:43:42,953 --> 00:43:45,756
And every now and then,
we do something called art therapy.

656
00:43:47,057 --> 00:43:48,626
You're really a teacher here?

657
00:43:50,227 --> 00:43:51,095
I'm not a teacher.

658
00:43:54,198 --> 00:43:57,835
There are all kinds of kids, and they each
have their own unique struggles,

659
00:43:58,636 --> 00:44:00,804
so I try my best to understand them,

660
00:44:01,905 --> 00:44:02,840
but it’s difficult.

661
00:44:19,790 --> 00:44:21,992
Is this Sora?

662
00:44:29,767 --> 00:44:30,601
Sora

663
00:44:31,669 --> 00:44:33,537
hasn't been able to go to school yet.

664
00:44:37,174 --> 00:44:38,142
Hey…

665
00:44:42,546 --> 00:44:44,114
I want to talk

666
00:44:45,215 --> 00:44:46,350
with Sora.

667
00:44:49,620 --> 00:44:51,288
I have to ask Sora first.

668
00:44:51,789 --> 00:44:53,290
Daddy.

669
00:44:57,127 --> 00:44:59,163
Daddy, come with me.

670
00:45:05,369 --> 00:45:07,270
‎THIS DRAMA IS FICTIONAL

671
00:45:07,271 --> 00:45:08,572
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita
